article.headline: Sacred Heart 28, Marist 16
article.story: POUGHKEEPSIE, N.Y. -- Dale Fink threw for 281 yards and three touchdowns Saturday as Sacred Heart defeated Marist 28-16. Steve Tedesco led the Pioneers' receiving corps with seven catches for 113 yards and one touchdown. Evin Jones ran for 101 yards on 17 attempts with one touchdown. Tony Patterson and Rich Rossi also had touchdown receptions for Sacred Heart (4-0). James LaMacchia started the scoring for Marist (1-3) with a four-yard catch in the second quarter to give the Red Foxes an early 6-0 lead. Chris Debowski finished with 13 completions on 28 attempts, throwing for 170 yards with a touchdown and an interception. Bo Ehikioya's one-yard touchdown run in the fourth quarter cut the Pioneers' lead to 21-16, but Marist was unable to come up with a defensive stop on Sacred Heart's ensuing drive. Ehikioya's score was the 41st of his career, tying a school record. He finished the day with 62 yards on 16 attempts.
